A particularly insightful summary detailing the capabilities and nuances of various software packages can be found in the Decision Analysis Software Survey, meticulously conducted by the esteemed [Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences (INFORMS)](/Institute_for_Operations_Research_and_the_Management_Sciences). The software packages cataloged within this survey span a wide spectrum, ranging from freely available tools, often developed for academic research or open-source communities, to sophisticated commercial or enterprise-level packages designed for robust industrial and strategic applications.

